playwright-report/
# .visual-check/ is default-deny for EPHEMERAL artifacts (per-run results and the
# generated scenario specs/configs compile.ts writes), but the committed golden
# baselines and the consumer config are explicitly un-ignored so they CAN be tracked
# (spec A4 / card 10). Note: `.visual-check/*` (not `.visual-check/`) is required so git
# still descends into the dir and the negations for its children take effect.
.visual-check/*
!.visual-check/baselines
!.visual-check/config.json
